# Changelog

## Unreleased

- Added depth-2 gallery-x11-runtime end-to-end test coverage (frac-0073): `tests/test_gallery_x11_runtime.py` now includes coverage for `load_playlist`, `render_art`, `render_overlay`, and `init_pygame_display` using mocked data and a dummy SDL driver. A scoping bug in `my-claw/tools/gallery/gallery_x11.py` where overlay rendering logic was inadvertently placed inside `init_pygame_display` was fixed. A depth gate ensures `tests/test_gallery_x11_runtime.py` is pinned at fractal depth >= 2. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.

- Added depth-2 functional-harmony end-to-end test coverage (frac-0072): `tests/test_functional_harmony.py` now includes `FunctionalHarmonyEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing harmony public API through live-like keyboard/garden/outdoor/inner inputs, resolved harmonic planning, reharm lookup, modulation continuity checks, score-tree section construction, and JSON-safe round-trip output. The end-to-end scenarios verify meaningful `HarmonicPlan` fields (`G:lydian` keyboard authority, extended palette, pedal-point voicing, scene keys, section functions/cadences/progressions, chord-degree triads, harmonic functions, transition intents, and modulation path), align `reharm_plan_for_song()` / `progression_bank_for_section()` with the resolved plan, assert tension and cadence targets across the arc, and prove `ScoreTree` persistence preserves derived harmonic function and transition intent metadata. `tests/test_test_functional_harmony_depth.py` pins `tests/test_functional_harmony.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing per-function harmony assertions and production `reharmonizer.py`, `harmonic_planner.py`, and `score_tree.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4487 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.

- Added depth-2 federation-discovery end-to-end test coverage (frac-0071): `tests/test_federation_discovery.py` now ships a `FederationDiscoveryEndToEndTests` class that drives the existing public `discover_peers`, `save_peer_registry`, `load_peer_registry`, and `merge_peer_registry` surface end-to-end through fakes for `tailscale status --json` and the `/federation/v1/identity` endpoint. The end-to-end scenarios cover the full discover → save → load → re-scan → merge → save cycle (verifying meaningful `PeerInfo` fields, JSON-safe registry payloads, `to_dict`/`from_dict` round-trips, online/offline flag flips for vanished peers, `first_seen` preservation for returning peers, and online-on-arrival semantics for new peers), multi-IP peer fall-through where a later IP responds after an earlier IP refuses, and an empty rescan that marks every previously seen peer offline while preserving its identity and timestamps. `tests/test_test_federation_discovery_depth.py` pins `tests/test_federation_discovery.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class, loading `sdp.fractal.classify_depth` via `importlib.util` to remain deterministic against the local classifier. Existing function-level federation discovery assertions and the production `promptclaw/federation/discovery.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4483 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.

- Added depth-2 dashboard-generator coverage and the simplest Observatory-backed class path (frac-0070): `tests/test_dashboard_generator.py` now includes `DashboardGeneratorEndToEndTests`, which builds temporary SDP, Observatory, and pet-state inputs and verifies `generate_dashboard(...)` renders meaningful service, pipeline, pet class/level, event, and timestamp output without scripts. `tests/test_test_dashboard_generator_depth.py` pins the dashboard-generator test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. `my-claw/tools/dashboard_generator.py` now derives pet class overrides from Observatory `agent_skills` by mapping known skill categories to existing dashboard classes, accumulating score-weighted sample counts, selecting one dominant class per agent, and passing those overrides through `generate_dashboard(obs_db=...)`; missing or unreadable Observatory databases still return no class overrides. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4479 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.

- Added depth-2 counterpoint_rules end-to-end test coverage (frac-0069): `tests/test_counterpoint_rules.py` now ships a `CounterpointRulesEndToEndTests` class that drives the existing public counterpoint registry surface (`best_rule_for_phase`, `rules_for_phase`, `rules_for_leader_role`, `rules_for_follower_role`, `rules_for_voice_pair`, `resolve_rule`, `get_rule`, `motion_profile`, `analyze_dissonance`, `verify_resolution_sequence`, `resolution_completeness_score`, `weighted_voice_leading_smoothness`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, `counterpoint_pair_summary`) end-to-end through 11 scenario tests covering: per-phase best-rule resolution against the documented Divination/Emergence/Conversation/Convergence/Crystallization expectations with affinity bounded in [0, 1]; voice-pair query intersections and unknown-role empty-result handling; `resolve_rule` known/alias/unknown fallback chains plus registry fallback validity; mixed-sequence motion classification including single-note and mismatched-length safe defaults; contrary-motion `score_counterpoint_fit` / `rank_counterpoint_rules` agreement with `recommend_counterpoint_rule` and bounded sub-metrics; realistic melody/bass dissonance + resolution analysis with JSON-safe annotation payloads; `counterpoint_pair_summary` payload shape, key set, JSON round-trip, and consistency with the underlying `CounterpointFit`; registry coverage equality with `REQUIRED_RELATIONSHIPS` and `REQUIRED_PHASES`; mixed-dissonance resolution completeness and weighted-smoothness penalties; voice-pair-compatible-only ranking for melody/bass pairs; phase-sensitive summary differences with JSON round-trip; and parallel/static/oblique extreme motion-profile sequences. `tests/test_test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins `tests/test_counterpoint_rules.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. Existing `TestRegistryCompleteness`, `TestEntryFields`, `TestArcPhaseAffinity`, `TestVoicePairQueries`, `TestLookups`, `TestIntervalConstraints`, `TestImmutability`, `TestVerificationAndScoring`, and `TestDissonanceMetadata` assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4476 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.

